2-18-102. Definitions.

(a) As used in this chapter:

(i) "Grantee beneficiary" or "grantee" means the person to whom an owner grants an interest in the real property that is the subject of the transfer on death deed;

(ii) "Owner" means a person who executes a transfer on death deed as provided in W.S. 2-18-103;

(iii) "Successor grantee beneficiary" means the person to whom an owner grants an interest in the real property that is the subject of the transfer on death deed if the primary grantee beneficiary does not survive the owner;

(iv) "Transfer on death deed" means a deed authorized by W.S. 2-18-103.
